N1Ex1
- to COMPILE my file :from my main/java directory, use the following command (org being the name of my package):
javac org\SortingFiles.java
to EXECUTE it : (if we want to print assets directory, you may choose another path)
java org.SortingFiles ..\..\..\src\assets\

N1Ex2
- to COMPILE my file : from my main/java directory :(org is my package name inside java directory) :
javac -d bin org\DirectoryTree.java
- to EXECUTE : (if we want to print assets directory, you may choose another path)
java -cp bin org.DirectoryTree ..\..\assets (from java , we step back to main then src and down to assets)

N1Ex3:
- to COMPILE my file : from my main/java directory :(org is my package name inside java directory) :
javac -d bin org\TreeInTxtFile.java
- to EXECUTE :(if we want to print assets directory, you may choose another path)
java -cp bin org.TreeInTxtFile ..\..\assets (from java , we step back to main then src and down to assets)


N1Ex4:
- to COMPILE my file : from my main/java directory :(org is my package name inside java directory) :
javac -d bin org\PrintFile.java
- to EXECUTE :(if we want to print assets directory, you may choose another path)
java -cp bin org.PrintFile ..\..\assets (from java , we step back to main then src and down to assets)

N1Ex5 :
- to COMPILE my file : from my main/java directory :(org is my package name inside java directory) :
javac -d bin org/*
- to EXECUTE
java -cp bin org.Main


